        "title": "Board > Add Tasks to Board",
        "excerpt":"Add existing tasks   Add tasks from the board view   In the Board view, click on the + sign at the top right corner of each column.      Tip: You can use the filter bar or simply type in the search bar to narrow down your task list.      Note: If the task you are adding to the board has already been given a status in the list view, there might be status change.   Add tasks from the list view   You can right-click to choose Add to board and select a board.   Hitting ^ on the keyboard then use the up/down arrow key to choose which board you want to add to can also allow you to add a task to the board.      Note: If the project doesn’t have a board, you would need to create a board first, in order to add the task to a board.   Create new tasks   In the Board view, click on the + sign at the top right corner of each column.   Hit Enter to continue to add new tasks. When done, hit Esc to finish.      Note: The newly created tasks will also be added to the list view as a root task.   Drag and drop tasks across columns   You can drag and drop your tasks from column to column to reorganize your work or move it to the next status.   Or you can drag the tasks up and down to reorder your column list.         Edit the task cover   If you had attached or embedded an image to a task, you can let it show as a task cover image in the board.      Click on the options icon on the top right corner of the task in your board. Select Edit cover and choose the image that you would like to show as a cover.      ","categories": ["add","tasks","to","board"],
