        "title": "Import & Export > Import via Copying and Paste",
        "excerpt":"You can copy and paste your work to Quire as tasks, to save you trouble from entering them one by one.   For example, you can copy a bullet list from a Word file or Notepad, an email content in Gmail, or a tabular data in Excel spreadsheet and CSV file, and then paste it to Quire.   Hit Ctrl + C (or ⌘ + C for Mac) to copy the content.      Go to your Quire project, click on a task and right click to select Paste or hit Ctrl+ V (or ⌘ + V for Mac).      If everything looks good, click Paste, or you can hit Ctrl + V again.   Read more on our blog about migrating to Quire via copy &amp; paste.  ","categories": ["import","via","copy","and","paste"],
