        "title": "Project > Move Project",
        "excerpt":"Duplicate a project   You may have an organization with similar projects.   Quire lets you duplicate a project, so you can use it as a template for new projects.   Click on the arrow beside the project name, and select Duplicate in the context menu.      Or go to the project’s Settings, and select Duplicate project at the bottom of the Options tab in Advanced.      Next, name your new project and choose the organization it belongs to.      Transfer a project   You may have projects belonging to the wrong organization.   Click on the arrow beside the project name, and select Transfer in the context menu.      Or go to the project’s Settings, and select Transfer project at the bottom of the Options tab in Advanced.      Next, choose the organization you want the project to be transferred to.      ","categories": ["duplicate","transfer","project"],
