        "excerpt":"Refer to tasks   You can refer to a task by simply typing #taskname or #taskid in the description or comment.      Tip: Toggle on the Advanced mode by hitting Ctrl or Alt for Mac to see the task ID number.   If you want to refer to tasks from a different project, type in #projectID/taskID or copy and paste the entire URL of that task.   Refer to projects   You can refer to a project by simply typing #projectid/0 in the description or comment.   You will be able to find the project ID at its URL. It’s the characters between w/ and /.   Tip: You can change your project ID by clicking on the arrow beside your project’s name at the top of your workspace. Scroll down to Project URL.  ","categories": ["refer","tasks","projects"],
